Social and technological advances make it possible for a growing part of humanity to access, create, modify, publish and distribute various kinds of works. By exercising those new possibilities a wealth of collectively re-usable works can be created. The easier it is to re-use and derive works, the richer our cultures become. We have a genuine interest in favoring an ecosystem where works can be spread, re-used and derived in creative ways, to ensure the graceful functioning of this ecosystem.
